title: LOOK: Bautista's go-ahead Game 5 homer brings down the house
text:
LOOK: Bautista's go-ahead Game 5 homer brings down the house Mike Axisa, CBS Sports 7:51 p.m. EDT October 14, 2015 Jose Bautista hit a clutch three-run home run in Game 5. (Photo: Nick Turchiaro-USA TODAY Sports) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
We're going to be talking about Game 5 of the ALDS for a long, long time. 
One inning after the Rangers took a 3-2 lead on a controversial play ( GameTracker ), the Blue Jays rallied to tie the game and then take a 6-3 lead. Three (three!) Elvis Andrus misplays opened the floodgates for the Blue Jays. 
Jose Bautista , the heart and soul of this Blue Jays team, gave his club the lead with a monstrous three-run home run. The Rogers Centre crowd went bonkers. 
That is the biggest home run in Toronto since Joe Carter's walk-off job in the 1993 World Series. No hyperbole there. 
Also, make sure you check out Bautista's savage bat flip: — Getty Images Sport (@GettySport) October 14, 2015 Jose Bautista is the absolute best. pic.twitter.com/r5wulmsXBq — Ian Hunter (@BlueJayHunter) October 14, 2015 
Gosh. And to think, people say baseball is boring.
